fix(av): late-cam acquisition no longer disposes + rebuilds the mesh

P0 pilot smoke regression: tutor grants mic first -> mesh builds with
audio-only -> tutor later clicks "Allow camera" -> entire mesh disposes
+ rebuilds from scratch -> remote peer's audio + video drop for 5-10s
while the new mesh re-negotiates. If the tutor ends the session before
the rebuild stabilizes, the recording mixdown contains only tutor audio
(son's audioStream was disconnected from addRemoteAudio when the mesh
tore down, and the rebuild's new son-audioStream arrived too late to be
recorded).

Root cause: useLiveAV's mesh-build effect had
[syncClient, localAudioStream, localVideoStream, localPeerId, sessionId]
as its dep array. Stream identity change (null -> MediaStream) flagged
a re-run, executed as cleanup + run-fresh -> full teardown.

Fix:
1. Introduce hasEverHadLocalMedia state - latches true the first time
   either stream becomes non-null, never goes back to false.
   Mesh-build effect depends on this boolean instead of stream identity.
2. peer-mesh adds addLocalTrackToAllPeers(track). Iterates every
   existing peer connection and pc.addTrack(track), idempotent on
   track id via pc.getSenders(). Each addTrack fires
   onnegotiationneeded, which the existing perfect-negotiation handler
   turns into a fresh offer -> answer cycle. Remote peers' already-
   flowing tracks stay live throughout; they see only a brief SDP
   refresh.
3. New useLiveAV effect with deps [localAudioStream, localVideoStream]
   calls mesh.addLocalTrackToAllPeers for every track in the current
   streams.

Tests: addLocalTrackToAllPeers x 4 in peer-mesh.test.ts (fan-out,
idempotency, disposed no-op, ended-track no-op) + mic-then-cam and
cam-then-mic regressions in useLiveAV.dom.test.tsx that assert
mesh.dispose is called exactly once per hook lifetime regardless of
acquisition order. All 43 useLiveAV tests pass, all 36 peer-mesh tests
pass, 994 of 1002 tests pass project-wide (8 failures are pre-existing
PG-unreachable suites unrelated to this change).
